Liverpool star, Mohamed Salah, has named the Super Eagles player he respects so much ahead of Nigeria vs Egypt Africa Cup of Nations tie. Salah said he respects Super Eagles captain, Ahmed Musa very well and will not exchange words with the Nigeria captain. Musa had during one of his interviews ahead of the clash, said that Nigeria’s Samuel Chukwueze was more dangerous than the Egyptian icon. Gabon Clinch 1-0 Victory Over Debutants Comoros Despite… AFCON: Ighalo Finally Announces Absence, Wishes Super Eagles… The Liverpool forward spoke during a pre-match press conference when asked to react to Musa’s comments. “I don’t think there is a need to reply to him because he is someone I respect so much. “Super Eagles have a good team but we would do our best to defeat them. “Both teams have good players, they have the chance to win. We will do our best to win tomorrow.”